-Cut off top 1" of artichoke
-In a pot, mix
4 cups of water
shot of olive oil
2 shots of white wine
lots of thyme
lots of coarse ground pepper
salt
crushed red pepper
oregano
bay leaf
garlic
half lemon (put the whole thing in there)

-Bring broth to a boil
-Once boiling, place artichoke in water (cut side down) and reduce temperature to a simmer
-Cover the pot and let simmer for ~30 minutes

Aioli:
-2 teaspoons of Hampton Creek Mayo (I used sriracha flavor)
-dash of Sriracha
-1/2 teaspoon of stoneground mustard
-take the lemon from the artichoke broth and squeeze the juice out of it and let the pulp fall in